import{_ as t,o,c as r,a as n,d as e,e as a,b as c}from"./app-de7a4551.js";const s={},i=e("h1",{id:"why-is-it-so-hard-to-get-effective-birth-control-in-the-us-1",tabindex:"-1"},[e("a",{class:"header-anchor",href:"#why-is-it-so-hard-to-get-effective-birth-control-in-the-us-1","aria-hidden":"true"},"#"),a(" Why Is It So Hard to Get Effective Birth Control in the US (1)")],-1),p=c('<p>About eight years ago, I met a young woman.<br> I&#39;ll call her Sophia. And she showed me her newborn in her lap.<br> And she said to me, &quot;This wasn&#39;t my plan.&quot;<br> She described how her <code>unplanned</code> <code>pregnancy</code> forced her to <em>drop out</em> of community college,<br> how she then lost her job<br> and was now living with her mother in Texas.<br> Sophia had already had two unplanned children before this third child was born.<br> All three of Sofia&#39;s pregnancies occurred while she was <em>on the pill</em>.<br> It was a birth control method that just didn&#39;t work for her, but it was the only method she&#39;d ever been offered.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 大约八年以前，我遇到了一个年轻的女士。<br> 我会以索菲亚来代称她<br> 她向我展示了两腿中的新生儿。<br> 并跟我说 “这并不是我计划中的一部分。”<br> 她描述了她未计划的怀孕是如何迫使她从社区大学中退学，<br> 失去工作，<br> 并和她母亲一起住在德州。<br> 在第三个孩子之前，索菲亚已经有了两个未计划的孩子。<br> 索菲亚的三次怀孕都在她吃避孕药的时候发生。<br> 这种避孕方式明显对她无效，但是这是她可以使用的唯一一种避孕方法。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> drop out -&gt; 退出（学校、组织或计划）<br> on the pill -&gt; 吃避孕药</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> unplanned<br><code>英 [ˌʌnˈplænd]美 [ˌʌnˈplænd]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 意外的；在计划外的；未经筹划的</p></blockquote><p>pregnancy [ 复数 pregnancies ]<br><code>英 [ˈpreɡnənsi]美 [ˈpreɡnənsi]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 怀孕（期），妊娠（期）</p></blockquote></details><p>Sophia&#39;s pregnancies weren&#39;t just unplanned.<br> She actively planned not to become pregnant and took <code>precautions</code> against it.<br> But the only method she was ever offered failed her.<br> In the US each year, nearly half of all pregnancies are unplanned.<br> I know it&#39;s an <code>astonishing</code> number to <em>get your head around</em>.<br> And over the span of ten years,<br> it&#39;s been <code>estimated</code> that six out of ten typical birth-control pill users will become accidentally pregnant.<br> This is not just about <code>uninformed</code> teens.<br> Most unplanned pregnancies occur to women who are in their 20s.<br> In fact, about half of all unplanned pregnancies occur to women who are actually using birth control, like Sophia.<br> Most people know about pills and condoms.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 索菲亚的怀孕并不只是计划外的。<br> 她刻意计划避免怀孕并使用了预防措施。<br> 但她仅有的一种方法并不奏效。<br> 在美国每年，将近一半的怀孕都不是计划中的。<br> 我知道这个数字听起来很惊人。<br> 并且在过去的10年内，<br> 有人预估十分之六的避孕药使用者会意外的怀孕。<br> 这并不仅仅是不懂事的年轻人。<br> 大部分意外怀孕发生在20多岁的女士身上。<br> 事实上，接近一半的意外怀孕发生在使用避孕药的女士身上，就像索菲亚。<br> 大部分知道避孕药和避孕套。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> get your head around -&gt; 理解；接受</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> precaution [ 复数 precautions ]<br><code>英 [prɪˈkɔːʃ(ə)n]美 [prɪˈkɔːʃn]</code><br> n. 预防措施，防备；避孕措施（precautions）</p><p>astonishing<br><code>英 [əˈstɒnɪʃɪŋ]美 [əˈstɑːnɪʃɪŋ]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 惊人的，令人惊讶的<br> v. 使惊奇，使惊讶（astonish 的现在分词）</p></blockquote><p>estimate ( estimating, estimated, estimates )<br><code>英 [ˈestɪmət; ˈestɪmeɪt]美 [ˈestɪmət; ˈestɪmeɪt]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 估计；判断，评价<br> n. 估计，估价；估价单；看法，判断</p></blockquote><p>uninformed<br><code>英 [ˌʌnɪnˈfɔːmd]美 [ˌʌnɪnˈfɔːrmd]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 无知的；未被通知的；未受教育的；不学无术的</p></blockquote></details><p>There are actually 18 FDA-<code>approved</code> methods of birth control,<br> each with different efficacy and <em>side effect</em> <code>profiles</code>,<br> some of which are 20 times more effective than others.<br> The reason you don&#39;t know about this is simple.<br> Outside of <em>specialty family planning clinics</em> that are <em>few and far between</em>,<br><em>health care organizations</em> don&#39;t educate people about all their birth control options and don&#39;t make them easily available.<br> But this is what <code>Upstream</code>, the <code>nonprofit</code> I <code>cofounded</code>, does.<br> We train <em>community health centers</em>, hospital <code>practices</code>, primary care <code>facilities</code>,<br> the places where the <em><code>vast</code> majority</em> of people get their <em>health care</em>,<br> to put patient centered needs first and provide <em>best in class</em> <code>contraceptive</code> care as a part of basic primary health care.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 实际上有18个FDA批准的避孕方式，<br> 每一个都有不同的效果和副作用，<br> 有些方法的效果是其他的20倍。<br> 你不知道它们的原因很简单。<br> 除了稀少的计划生育诊所，<br> 医疗中心并不提供关于避孕方法的科普也不轻易提供这些服务。<br> 但这正是上游，我建立的非营利组织，所做的事情。<br> 我们为社区诊所，医院，保荐机构，<br> 大部分人看医生的地方，<br> 提供科普，并把最好的避孕服务像基本医疗一样提供，做到了把患者的需求放到第一位。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> side effect -&gt; 副作用<br> specialty family planning clinics -&gt; 专科计划生育诊所 few and far between -&gt; 罕见的、稀少的<br> health care organizations -&gt; 保健组织<br> community health centers -&gt; 社区卫生中心<br> vast majority -&gt; 绝大多数<br> health care -&gt; 医疗保健<br> best in class -&gt; 同类中最好的</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> approve ( approving, approved, approves )<br><code>英 [əˈpruːv]美 [əˈpruːv]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 同意，赞成；批准，通过；核准；喜欢，赞赏；&lt;古&gt;证明，显示；使（废品或公共土地）升值</p></blockquote><p>profile<br><code>英: [ˈprəʊfaɪl] 美: [ˈproʊˌfaɪl]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 轮廓；简介；形象；外形<br> v. 扼要介绍；概述；写简介</p></blockquote><p>upstream<br><code>英 [ˌʌpˈstriːm]美 [ˌʌpˈstriːm]</code></p><blockquote><p>adv. 向（在）上游；逆流地<br> adj. 向（在）上游的；逆流而上的</p></blockquote><p>nonprofit<br><code>英 [ˌnɒnˈprɒfɪt]美 [ˌnɑːnˈprɑːfɪt]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 非营利的；不以营利为目的</p></blockquote><p>co-found<br><code>英: [kəʊ&#39;faʊndə] 美: [koʊ&#39;faʊndə]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 共同创立</p></blockquote><p>practice<br><code>英 [ˈpræktɪs]美 [ˈpræktɪs]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 实践，实际操作；通常的做法，惯例；练习；练习课，固定的训练时间；（医生、律师或其他专业人士的）业务，事务所；诉讼手续，诉讼程序<br> v. 练习；经常做，养成……的习惯；信奉（宗教）；（医生、律师等）执业，从业</p></blockquote><p>facility [ 复数 facilities ]<br><code>英 [fəˈsɪləti]美 [fəˈsɪləti]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 设施，设备；卫生间；天赋，才能；（机器等的）特别装置，（服务等的）特色；（用作某种用途的）场所</p></blockquote><p>contraceptive [ 复数 contraceptives ]<br><code>英 [ˌkɒntrəˈseptɪv]美 [ˌkɑːntrəˈseptɪv]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 避孕用具；避孕药；避孕方法<br> adj. 避孕的</p></blockquote></details>',6);function d(l,b){return o(),r("div",null,[i,n(" 为什么在美国避孕这么难（1）  "),p])}const u=t(s,[["render",d],["__file","27-birth-control-1.html.vue"]]);export{u as default};
